{"repo": "fatedier/frp", "pr_number": 3404, "type": "review_comment", "body": "This change has the potential to break the e2e case located at https://github.com/fatedier/frp/blob/dev/test/e2e/basic/client_server.go#L100. \r\n\r\nWe would like to avoid making any incompatible changes.\r\n\r\nIn my opinion, `tls over websocket` is not equivalent to `wss`. \r\n\r\nTherefore, if we intend to support wss, it would be better to move it from the protocol to the proxy parameter.", "createdAt": "2023-04-13T11:29:47Z", "author": "fatedier"}
{"repo": "fatedier/frp", "pr_number": 3404, "type": "review", "body": "", "state": "COMMENTED", "createdAt": "2023-04-13T15:03:12Z", "author": "Dirbaio"}
{"repo": "fatedier/frp", "pr_number": 3404, "type": "review_comment", "body": "oh okay! I didn't realize \"TLS over websocket\" was actually a desired combination. \r\n\r\nCan you clarify which exact `frpc.ini` settings should result in \"websocket over TLS\"? I'll update the code to match that. Thanks!", "createdAt": "2023-04-13T15:03:12Z", "author": "Dirbaio"}
{"repo": "fatedier/frp", "pr_number": 3404, "type": "review", "body": "", "state": "COMMENTED", "createdAt": "2023-04-15T05:00:26Z", "author": "fatedier"}
{"repo": "fatedier/frp", "pr_number": 3404, "type": "review_comment", "body": "Perhaps an alternative solution could be to add support for `wss` to the `protocol` parameter. \r\nIf the user configuration is set to `websocket`, it will remain unchanged. However, if the configuration is set to `wss`, the websocket and tls order can be adjusted to implement wss.\r\n\r\nWDYT?", "createdAt": "2023-04-15T05:00:26Z", "author": "fatedier"}
