{"repo": "fatedier/frp", "pr_number": 3737, "type": "review_comment", "body": "Why do we need these labels? What benefits will it bring?", "createdAt": "2023-10-31T11:43:51Z", "author": "fatedier"}
{"repo": "fatedier/frp", "pr_number": 3737, "type": "review_comment", "body": "What's the purpose of this script? What are the differences compared to the previous execution method?", "createdAt": "2023-10-31T11:47:18Z", "author": "fatedier"}
{"repo": "fatedier/frp", "pr_number": 3737, "type": "review_comment", "body": "Given that frp is often used to listen on port 80, will not using the root user have any impact? On the other hand, what problems may arise from using the root user?", "createdAt": "2023-10-31T11:48:24Z", "author": "fatedier"}
{"repo": "fatedier/frp", "pr_number": 3737, "type": "review", "body": "", "state": "COMMENTED", "createdAt": "2023-10-31T13:22:24Z", "author": "reneleonhardt"}
{"repo": "fatedier/frp", "pr_number": 3737, "type": "review_comment", "body": "It' best practice to use specific versions, and it's effectively the same version (at the moment).\r\nSo if a project decides to improve security by rebuilding images even without code change, then version numbers make it easier for humans to accept the suggestions dependabot makes.\r\nhttps://github.com/hadolint/hadolint/wiki/DL3007", "createdAt": "2023-10-31T13:22:24Z", "author": "reneleonhardt"}
{"repo": "fatedier/frp", "pr_number": 3737, "type": "review", "body": "", "state": "COMMENTED", "createdAt": "2023-10-31T13:26:08Z", "author": "reneleonhardt"}
{"repo": "fatedier/frp", "pr_number": 3737, "type": "review_comment", "body": "Best practice, a docker image tag is a also only a \"label\", those labels make it easier for your users what's inside this image.\r\nThe specific app version would be good too, but a bit harder to integrate in this case.\r\nhttps://snyk.io/blog/how-and-when-to-use-docker-labels-oci-container-annotations/", "createdAt": "2023-10-31T13:26:07Z", "author": "reneleonhardt"}
{"repo": "fatedier/frp", "pr_number": 3737, "type": "review", "body": "", "state": "COMMENTED", "createdAt": "2023-10-31T13:28:56Z", "author": "reneleonhardt"}
{"repo": "fatedier/frp", "pr_number": 3737, "type": "review_comment", "body": "The reason for introducing this script was the unification of the 2 Dockerfiles into 1.\r\nIt's not allowed to use ARG/ENV variables inside ENTRYPOINT, your binaries have different names, it's best practice to create a minimal `exec` script in this case.\r\nI will improve it a bit to make hadolint happy 😄", "createdAt": "2023-10-31T13:28:56Z", "author": "reneleonhardt"}
{"repo": "fatedier/frp", "pr_number": 3737, "type": "review", "body": "", "state": "COMMENTED", "createdAt": "2023-10-31T13:34:48Z", "author": "reneleonhardt"}
{"repo": "fatedier/frp", "pr_number": 3737, "type": "review_comment", "body": "Using root opens the attack surface to a whole lot more security bug possibilities.\r\nThe privileged port problem was solved 3 years ago:\r\nhttps://stackoverflow.com/questions/66431299/i-can-bind-to-port-80-as-a-non-root-user-in-a-docker-container-why-whats-goin \r\nCan you try both new images to verify the expected functionality?\r\n\r\nIt would be optimal if the Docker build would automatically verify the expected functionality... 😉", "createdAt": "2023-10-31T13:34:48Z", "author": "reneleonhardt"}
{"repo": "fatedier/frp", "pr_number": 3737, "type": "review", "body": "", "state": "COMMENTED", "createdAt": "2023-11-01T07:44:26Z", "author": "fatedier"}
{"repo": "fatedier/frp", "pr_number": 3737, "type": "review_comment", "body": "I do not prefer to add these redundant information.", "createdAt": "2023-11-01T07:44:26Z", "author": "fatedier"}
